{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1511198828,"nonce":"q2trokJOma11yEWzym0zRwMW4Ww=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNzU0MzY0NTI=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1595","origin":"github"},"title":"MultiQC - Use \"element_identifier\" as \"sample name\" for all tools","message":"In order to take full advantage of MultiQC's aggregation report, it needs to find consistent sample names across various datasets. Thus, whenever possible, MultiQC should be using `element_identifier` as the \"sample name\". The way MultiQC parses the sample name varies for each tool. In some cases, the underlying tool must be updated to use the `element_identifier` (e.g. featureCounts https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/1583). This issue is intended to track the tools that do not properly parse the `element_identifier` when used with MultiQC. If someone can verify the status of a tool, please update this issue accordingly.\n\nVerified tools (checked tools properly use `element_identifier`):\n- [x] fastqc\n- [x] featureCounts - (tool is [fixed](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/1583), depends on Galaxy fix https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/pull/5049)\n- [x] rseqc\n- [ ] samtools\n    - [ ] stats ?\n    - [ ] flagstat ?\n    - [ ] idxstats - seems to use `name`\n    - [ ] rmdup ?\n- [x] star\n\nUnknown status (the status of `element_identifier` parsing for these tools is unverified):\n* bamtools\n* bcftools\n* bismark\n* bowtie2\n* busco\n* cutadapt\n* flexbar\n* gatk\n* hicup\n* hisat2\n* htseq\n* kallisto\n* picard\n* prokka\n* quast\n* rsem\n* salmon\n* samblaster\n* snpeff\n* sortmerna\n* tophat\n* trimmomatic\n* vcftools","files":null}]}